 stereotype Vorstellungen und liefert Materialien sowie theoretisch-methodische Ansätze, um sie zu hinterfragen.  afunded by Backlisttransformation EOSC Future  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aArbeitsmigration. 4aBild. 4aDiskurs. 4aFotografie. 4aIdentität. 4aKulturwissenschaft. 4aMedien. 4aMigration. 4aPostkolonialismus. 4aPrivatfotografie. 4aSozialgeschichte. 4aVisuelle Repräsentation. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Emigration & Immigration.2bisacsh  aCultural Studies.  aDiscourse.  aIdentity.  aImage.  aLabour Migration.  aMedia.  aMigration.  aPhotography.  aPostcolonialism.  aPrivat Photography.  aSocial History.  aVisual Representation.2 aBacklisttransformation EOSC Futureefunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2020 Part 2z978311069629508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Complete eBook Package 2020z9783111025124oZDB-23-TGP40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783839454978?locatt=mode:legacyzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839454978zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839454978/original  a978-3-11-069629-5 DG Plus PP Package 2020 Part 2b2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA  aZDB-23-TGPb2020